metadata.description:
Deconstructed structure built from many blocks in isometric view.


——

- Press [s] in live mode to export a PNG file.

- By adding a ‘scale’ parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 4 with a default value of 1.

metadata.name: Punktwelt #440
metadata.description:
Continuing on the theme of color perception in Farbteiler, Punktwelt is an exploration of color interaction, projection and perceived depth, and the aesthetics of simple Boolean operations on form.

Each shape is the result of a single block, a rectangular cuboid, subjected to a series of Boolean subtractions with other blocks, and rendered in parallel projection, oblique or axonometric, in the abstract landscape of the Punktwelt.

Some have horizons, some have banded or striped backgrounds. The unnatural drawing order and chromatic differences of the individual faces sometimes yields illusory or paradoxical visual geometries.

Press ’s’ to save a png. Press ’4’ to export a high resolution png. Press ’8’ to export a very high resolution png. Press ’e’ to export an SVG file (may take some time and produce large files).

Aspect ratio variations are 4:5, 5:4, 2:3, 3:2 and 1:1.

Built in Javascript with p5.js, p5.svg and csg.js.

metadata.name: Blocky-Neon #13
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Blocky-Neon' is a colorful play on perspective and geometry.

Each output plays with color, and the absence of color, highlighted by stark white lines against a dark background.

To download a 1500x2000px PNG:
Click/tap 'open', then click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear.

metadata.name: Minimalist #21
metadata.description:
This abstract art is produced by exercising concepts of minimalism. Each artwork is composed of simple figures and simple engaging colors. 

Each abstract art piece is generated to connect with a specific type of person. When the viewer sees an abstract image that resonates with him or her a connection is made. 

This artwork was produced using computer graphics software and randomly layerd images.

metadata.name: Symbology437 #52
metadata.description:
Abstract, distorted compositions using symbols from the original IBM VGA codepage 437 character set. The symbols were created in code as bitmaps, scaled, and then drawn onto the canvas. The shading is based on the characters and sets from ANSI and ASCII art styles. 

There are 4 main types of outputs:
- Abstracts, 50%
- Random characters, 25%
- One of 16 preset character layouts, 25%
- One of 16 custom symbol PFP styles that will be 10% of the total outputs

For abstracts, there are several main styles created from layering different base shapes: circles, filled circles, rectangles, flow field lines, and rain-like streaks.

Color combinations include monochromatic, green or amber, dark mode, and multicolor.

Press 's' to save the image. The size is 2318x3000px, and for PFPs, the size is 3000x3000px.

metadata.name: Specter👻Pixel◼Latte☕ #98
metadata.description:
Bleached dimensions, creamy pixels, colorful apparitions, void zones and uneventful dances. A group of specters (A.K.A. circles that trail) attempt to accompany, comfort, entertain, hypnotize, console and soothe you. 

NOTE: Requires browsers and devices which support Float32 textures. Firefox has been most reliable.

Acknowledgements 
made with P5.js, p5Fbo by Adam Ferriss and noisejs by Josephg

metadata.name: Annum #2063
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: Canyon #117
metadata.description:
Canyon is a generative art project inspired by canyons and reinterpreted in 9 different styles (that each have their own specificities):
- Grand Canyon
- Radioactive
- Blue Grotto
- Black Crystals
- Magma
- Iceberg
- Imagination
- UV
- Sandstone

Accessories (Kayak, Rowing Boat, Barrels) are present on some variations (in this case, it is possible to generate a second variation without accessories by pressing "a").

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.
